shows that when we reason backward from $n_2$ to $n_1$, knowledge of
$\lambda$ does not make $n_2$ irrelevant; on the contrary, knowledge of
$n_2$ makes $\lambda$ irrelevant!
We could hardly make the point more strongly that *physical* dependence
and *logical* dependence are very different things. Some may find this
result so disconcerting that their first reaction is to doubt the
correctness of (11). If you find yourself with such feelings, please
